	•	Run Automator -> “New document”
	•	Choose a type of your document -> “Quick action”
	•	Set “Workflow receives” -> “no input” in “any application”
	•	Choose “Actions” -> “Utilities” -> “Run AppleScript” -> Double click
	•	Enter text from “Open new Finder window with shortcut.applescript” file
	•	File -> “Save” -> “NewFinderWindow” (for example)

	•	Go “System Preferences” -> “Keyboard” -> “Shortcuts” -> “General” -> “NewFinderWindow”
	•	Set shortcut -> “Command + ‘” (for example)
